    "As our result suggests, the explanation can assist individuals in understanding the suggestions, improve the rationale of recommendations, and improve transparency perception.",
    "On the contrary, the respondents in our study also expressed concerns regarding the adverse effects.",
    "For example, the findings suggest supervised, concise, and controlled dissemination of information to improve explanation representation and enhance understandability.",
    "Excessive information may frustrate the user and lead to cognitive overload.",
    "The features mentioned above represent competing aspects of explainable recommendations that can be considered as the affordance of explainable recommendations."
